900/8/200 = 15/4/5 = 0.75 degrees, as the product of 1 for 900, 8/200 for 1.6 for 4*5, and 8*5*385 = 92600 steps per rotation

The number of steps per rotation is 92600 steps per rotation / 1.6 degrees/step = 5737.5 steps/degree * 360 degrees/rotation = 2131440 (approximated to 1 s.f.)

2131440 steps / 1.8 * 1000 = 2200 stride angle (approximated to 1 s.f.)

2200 steps / 1.6 = 1388 stride angle (approximated to 1 s.f.)

1388 / 5 = 277.6 stride angle (approximated to 1 s.f.)

277.6 degrees (pre gearing) (approximated to 1 s.f.) * 7.2V stepper drivers * 2A = 146.08W (approximated to 1 s.f.)

6 * 146.08W (approximated to 1 s.f.) =    878.48W (approximated to 1 s.f.)

Another point to consider is that the steps are only theoretical, and in real use, there can be missed steps when the load is too heavy, the driver might not be powerful enough, and when the motor experiences too much heat, which can cause missed steps.
